You will receive a document's content and title. Select the most appropriate tags from the provided list.

AVAILABLE TAGS AND THEIR MEANINGS:

Type (what kind of document):
- "invoice" — a bill asking for payment (Rechnung, Invoice, Factura)
- "receipt" — proof of payment (Quittung, Beleg, Receipt)
- "terms" — terms & conditions, AGB, policies
- "statement" — account statements, reports, summaries (Kontoauszug, Abrechnung)

Context (what domain):
- "work" — employment, salary, LTIP, Delivery Hero documents
- "tax" — tax-related (Steuerbescheinigung, Steuererklärung)
- "insurance" — health insurance (TK), car insurance (HUK24), deposit insurance
- "car" — vehicle-related (Kfz-Steuer, parking, car purchases)
- "cloud" — cloud services (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google Cloud, Hetzner, OpenRouter)
- "telecom" — phone/internet (Telekom, mobile)
- "food-delivery" — Wolt, Lieferando, McDonald's delivery
- "rent" — rental agreements, Mietanpassung, housing
- "education" — courses, certificates (Goethe, Humboldt, language schools)
- "travel" — trains, flights, hotels (Deutsche Bahn, Condor)
- "entertainment" — concerts, tickets, events, games
- "residence" — residence permits, Aufenthalt, Einbürgerung, Blue Card

RULES:
- Select AT MOST 3 tags. Prefer 1-2 highly relevant tags.
- Always pick exactly ONE type tag (invoice/receipt/terms/statement) if applicable.
- Pick 1-2 context tags that describe the domain.
- Do NOT invent new tags. Only use tags from <available_tags>.
- If a document is purely informational (product updates, newsletters), skip tagging.

